Yes, so Miss Bailey is making us do a concrete poem, a thought which scared the hell out of me, but I have been warned about her "put you on the spot" tendancies. It should be ok though as I have asked around and no-one else seems to know what they are doing. Except Joni who came up with a pepper pot/engine sounds poem after 1 day. 

Well, I decided to do mine about memory, mainly because I was thinking about Miss Copeland's (is that how you spell it?) class while I was doing it and how I like her much more than Miss Bailey. Anyway, this is what I have come up with so far and I don't intend on spending much more time on it, so she better like it.

Also, I made it easy to read to avoid not being able to read it out without laughing. How smart am I?

You are Sloth! Lazy huh ?? You're a bit slow in getting going -
and tend not to do anything unless it is
absolutely necessary. You'd rather sit around,
watch TV/Sleep then go out and about with
friends, or take part in a sporting event. On
the positive side, you tend to be quite smart,
as you spend a lot of time watching the News
(!!) or on the computer, Also by conserving
your energy, it's right there waiting for you
when it's vitally important to get going. Consider possibly moving out of the room once in a
while - and perhaps once a week trade watching
TV for half an hour with a walk - and you'll be
back on track. However, Congratulations on being the most
intelligent of the 7 deadly sins...

Yeah, so this bloody weather is getting on my tits, bigstyle. I mean come on, has the earth swapped places with pluto or what???

So anyway, today was quite eventfull. I tagged along with the media studies people (Joni, Emma, Lauren, Christine and Flossie) while they were filming children in the park, bunch of perves if you ask me, but I did go along so I suppose I am just as bad, but not really. It was incredibly cold though, so Joni was quite the gentleman and gave me her scarf, how lovely. I do have a bit of frostbite around the bum area, but not to worry, I am sitting in a bowl of hot water.

After the park thing I went with my very good chum Emma (mentioned above) to the gym, that was very enjoyable, apart from in the changing rooms there was this woman in the shower and she came out all naked and what not, has she no shame? So I think for next time I may buy a blindfold for when I go in the changing room. One that had eyes on it so it looked like I wasn't wearing it. Or a pair of those glasses that you wear when you want to sleep in class, you know, the ones that have eyes on them. 

After that Emma and I went back to her house and she let me borrow her brand new copy of Mysterious Skin, I will be watching/perving over that once I am done here. I let her borrow my copy of The L Word though so I am not the only perve in the house, although, it is my copy....oh well. I hope Emma is watching it right now, and being aroused by the sex scenes, as I was. Only kidding....

Well, this entry seems to have become some kind of admital of perversities which I possess so I will stop here, I seem to have rambled rather alot.

I would like to thank Emma and Joni for commenting on my last post, however insulting they may have been (Joni), as I was scared that I would be one of those loner journal people who never gets posts and stuff, so thanks for that guys...how gay.

Cheerio xx
